<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE1416CCB9CECCBFDAF25A4" box="[474,541,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[161,1415,290,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-72@5.[151,1436,273,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left male tegmina of Acanthoplus discoidalis (CH8946), Acanthoproctus cervinus (CH8947), Hetrodes pupus (CHelb8948), Enyaliopsis bloyeti (CH8853), E. carolinus (CH8625), E. ephippiatus (CH7737), E. jennae (damaged; CH8267), Gymnoproctus rammei (CH8763), Eugasteroides loricatus (CH7352), Spalacomimus stettinenesis, S. talpa (CH7354), S. verruciferus (CH7188). Scale 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392715/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), stridulatory file (
<tableCitation id="1A7D036FFFE1416CC8A9ECCBFCF025A4" box="[751,834,1447,1473]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,239,332,356]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Body dimensions and characteristics of stridulatory files in Hetrodini" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0380665CFFF54178CAD1E820FC402101" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" tableUuid="0380665CFFF54178CAD1E820FC402101">Table 1</tableCitation>
), and spectrum of the song (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE1416CCEC5ECCBFB7425A7" box="[1155,1222,1447,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[171,1410,201,1247]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[151,1436,181,1263]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Power spectra of male calling songs in Hetrodini species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392725/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) do not show large differences to the typical 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE1416CCBE8ECA7FDAB2580" authorityName=", Kowalski &amp; Lakes-Harlan" authorityYear="2010" box="[430,537,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hetrodini">Hetrodini</taxonomicName>
pattern. The calling song consists of a long, uninterrupted trill (song 
<typeStatus id="88448876FFE1416CCF55ECA7FAF12580" box="[1299,1347,1483,1509]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">type</typeStatus>
A) with a SRR of about 22 Hz (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE1416CCBDBEC83FDB7266C" box="[413,517,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1322,1346]" captionTargetBox="[156,1433,260,1291]" captionTargetId="figure-48@14.[151,1436,237,1299]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Oscillograms of the calling songs in the genera Eugaster, Eugasteroides and Spalacomimus (figures of S. liberianus based on figures and data from literature; see text). A Eugaster guyoni, B Eugaster spinulosa, C Eugasteroides loricatus, D Spalacomimus liberianus, E Spalacomimus magnus, F Spalacomimus stettinensis, G Spalacomimus talpa, H Spalacomimus verruciferus, I Spalacomimus spec. near verruciferus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392739/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 10G</figureCitation>
; see 
<tableCitation id="1A7D036FFFE1416CC87DEC83FD22266C" box="[571,656,1519,1545]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,236,476,501]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 2. Song characteristics of Hetrodini species (for song type see Fig. 5 and text)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" tableUuid="0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE1416CCA81EF7EFC7C2634" blockId="23.[151,1436,1230,1725]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE1416CCA81EF7EFE8F2649" bold="true" box="[199,317,1554,1580]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Genitalia.</emphasis>
The genitalic sclerites are similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE1416CC97BEF7FFC652649" baseAuthorityName="Weidner" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[829,983,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Spalacomimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stettinensis">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE1416CC97BEF7FFC652649" box="[829,983,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">S. stettinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the lateral sclerites are even larger than in this species and the titillator is pointed at the tip (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE1416CC91CEF5BFC732634" box="[858,961,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1046,1070]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,272,1023]" captionTargetId="figure-69@15.[151,1436,272,1023]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 11. Titillators in the genus Spalacomimus. A S. magnus (Gulwe), B S. stettinensis (Lambo Estate), C S. stettinensis (neotype), D S. talpa (Lembeni), E S. verruciferus (Lake Chala), F S. spec. near verruciferus (Lossogonoi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392741/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE1416CCA81EF36FAA726D8" blockId="23.[151,1436,1230,1725]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE1416CCA81EF36FEC92611" bold="true" box="[199,379,1626,1652]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Chromosomes:</emphasis>
2n = 24 (22 +XY), FN = 24; pair 1–11 and both sex chromosomes acrocentric [
<specimenCount id="41F9FD5DFFE1416CCF50EF37FADD2610" box="[1302,1391,1627,1653]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" type="male">4 males</specimenCount>
described earlier (
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE1416CCB00EFECFD0A26FC" author="Warchalowska-Sliwa, E. &amp; Grzywacz, B. &amp; Maryanska-Nadachowska, A. &amp; Hemp, A. &amp; Hemp, C." box="[326,696,1662,1691]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref19417" refString="Warchalowska-Sliwa, E., Grzywacz, B., Maryanska-Nadachowska, A., Hemp, A. &amp; Hemp, C. (2015) Different steps in the evolution of neo-sex chromosomes in two East African Spalacomimus species (Orthoptera, Hetrodinae). European Journal of Entomology, 112 (1), 1 - 10. https: // doi. org / 10.14411 / eje. 2015.024" type="journal article" year="2015">
Warchałowska-Śliwa 
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE1416CC87BEF13FDC726FC" box="[573,629,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<collectingCountry id="2FE87644FFE1416CC882EF12FD5E26FC" box="[708,748,1662,1689]" name="Switzerland" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">CH</collectingCountry>
7354, 
<collectingCountry id="2FE87644FFE1416CC977EF12FCEB26FC" box="[817,857,1662,1689]" name="Switzerland" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">CH</collectingCountry>
7525, 
<collectingCountry id="2FE87644FFE1416CC9D8EF13FC7426FC" box="[926,966,1663,1689]" name="Switzerland" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">CH</collectingCountry>
7626, 
<collectingCountry id="2FE87644FFE1416CCE4AEF12FB8426FC" box="[1036,1078,1662,1689]" name="Switzerland" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">CH</collectingCountry>
7699)]; thin C-positive paracentromeric bands in all chromosomes and an interstitial one on the long pair and the neo-Y chromosome.
</paragraph>
